The paper discusses privacy concerns in social networks, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). It also proposes a query language for privacy policy authoring and enforcement, which involves database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the user-driven aspect of privacy policies, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the constantly evolving nature of social networks, which could fall under the category of complex systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a comprehensive conceptual model for privacy in social networks, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
